l\namplitudes and/or significant scatter in their light curves. Thus, some\neclipsing or rotating ellipsoidal variables might be present. However, we are\nconfident that the given periods are the correct ones. There seems to be a\npossible weak correlation between the rotational period and colour, in the\nsense that cooler magnetic CP stars rotate more slowly. However, this\ncorrelation seems to disappear when correcting for the interstellar reddening.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 4 Jul 2015 14:47:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-30"}
